Chí Kha is an Intern Backend Developer with foundational experience primarily gained through robust personal and academic projects, complemented by a 3-month Front-End Developer internship. Their core expertise centers on designing and implementing **RESTful APIs** and **Microservices**, with a strong focus on **JWT Authentication/Authorization**, **Caching** strategies using **Redis** and **Caffeine**, and **Asynchronous Task Handling** via **RabbitMQ**. Chí Kha has demonstrated proficiency in **System Design**, developing **Scalable Web Solutions**, and implementing **Real-time Chat** functionalities. Notable achievements include securing a Top 5 position in an IT Competency Assessment (Backend Track) and a Top 30 in the 'Code Your Future' IT Contest, underscoring a strong aptitude for backend development.
Technically, Chí Kha is proficient in backend development using **Java** with **Spring Boot**, **Python** with **FastAPI** and **Django**, and **PHP** with **Laravel 10**. They possess strong database skills in **MySQL**, **MongoDB**, and **Redis**, and are adept with **Docker** for containerization and **Git/GitHub** for **Version Control**. Experience extends to integrating third-party APIs such as **VNPay** sandbox for payment processing, **Google Drive API** for storage, **Google Cloud Vision API** for image analysis, and **Spring Mail/Gmail API** for email notifications. They are skilled in **Unit Testing** with **JUnit** and **Mockito**, implementing **WebSocket** for real-time communication, and developing **Responsive UI** with **React.js**, **TailwindCSS**, and **Bootstrap**. Further capabilities include **Data Structure and Algorithms**, **Object-Oriented Programming**, **Modular Design**, and **Automated Tests**, demonstrating a comprehensive understanding of modern software development practices.